<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFA7BA67FC9EF990FBAEF8CA" pageId="70" pageNumber="961" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA7BA67FC9EF990FAC6F88A" blockId="70.[835,1475,1571,1851]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA7BA67FC9EF990FC36F98A" bold="true" box="[835,955,1571,1595]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Carapace squarish; no epibranchial tooth present, lateral margin entire; posterolateral margins subparallel; outer surface of chela gently convex, covered with small squamiform granules, ventral margin of palm sinuous, serrated; suture between male thoracic sternites 3 and 4 undiscernible; male pleon broadly triangular; male sternopleonal cavity without press-button of pleonal locking mechanism on sternite 5; G1 slender, straight, relatively long chitinous distal part bent at almost right angles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA7BA67FC9EF8D0FBAEF8CA" blockId="70.[835,1059,1891,1915]" box="[835,1059,1891,1915]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA7BA67FC9EF8D0FC1EF8CA" bold="true" box="[835,915,1891,1915]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">Colour</emphasis>
. 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFA7BA67FC7EF8D0FC46F8CB" box="[931,971,1891,1914]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">Not</collectingRegion>
known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFA7BA66FC9EF810FD7CFDA4" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="962" pageId="70" pageNumber="961" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA7BA67FC9EF810FBF9F78A" blockId="70.[835,1474,1955,2107]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA7BA67FC9EF810FC26F80A" bold="true" box="[835,939,1955,1979]" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">Remarks</emphasis>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFA7BA67FC06F817FB7AF80A" baseAuthorityName="Miers" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[987,1271,1956,1979]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Miersarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="961" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granosimanum">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA7BA67FC06F817FB7AF80A" box="[987,1271,1956,1979]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="961">Miersarma granosimanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the entire surface of sternites 1–4 appears almost contiguous, without any trace of a ridge or suture. However, this surface is uneven and when dried, the separation between sternites 2 and 3 can just about be discerned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA6BA66FFACFF0EFD7DFE24" blockId="71.[113,753,189,405]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">
The G1 is characteristically long and slender, with an elongate distal part. The G1 is somewhat twisted; viewed from one angle, it appears almost straight (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="598786C5FFA6BA66FDC5FF4EFD3AFEA4" box="[536,695,253,277]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="67.[113,148,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,193,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-15@67.[83,1471,183,1594]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Fig. 40. Miersarma granosimanum. A–E, lectotype male (16.9 × 14.8 mm) (NHM 1880.6), Borneo; F–I, male (22.5 × 19.2 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.164), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia; J, male (19.5 × 16.7 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.165), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia. A, male pleon; B, F, left G1 (ventral view, denuded); C, G, J, left G1 (dorsal view, denuded); D, H, left distal part of G1 (ventral view, denuded); E, I, left distal part of G1 (dorsal view, denuded). Scales: A = 5.0 mm; B, C, F, G, J = 1.0 mm; D, E, H, I = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351367/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Fig. 40B, C, J</figureCitation>
), but when slightly adjusted, it appears distinctly sinuous (
<figureCitation id="598786C5FFA6BA66FD18FEAEFF4CFEE4" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="67.[113,148,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,193,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-15@67.[83,1471,183,1594]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Fig. 40. Miersarma granosimanum. A–E, lectotype male (16.9 × 14.8 mm) (NHM 1880.6), Borneo; F–I, male (22.5 × 19.2 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.164), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia; J, male (19.5 × 16.7 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.165), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia. A, male pleon; B, F, left G1 (ventral view, denuded); C, G, J, left G1 (dorsal view, denuded); D, H, left distal part of G1 (ventral view, denuded); E, I, left distal part of G1 (dorsal view, denuded). Scales: A = 5.0 mm; B, C, F, G, J = 1.0 mm; D, E, H, I = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351367/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Fig. 40F, G</figureCitation>
). In the 
<typeStatus id="1E0724E2FFA6BA66FEC0FE8EFEF2FEE4" box="[285,383,317,341]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">lectotype</typeStatus>
male, the G1 is in poor condition and slightly shrivelled, the subdistal part of the G1 appears slightly damaged, with a small flange visible (
<figureCitation id="598786C5FFA6BA66FDBFFECEFD69FE24" box="[610,740,381,405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="67.[113,148,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,193,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-15@67.[83,1471,183,1594]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Fig. 40. Miersarma granosimanum. A–E, lectotype male (16.9 × 14.8 mm) (NHM 1880.6), Borneo; F–I, male (22.5 × 19.2 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.164), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia; J, male (19.5 × 16.7 mm) (ZRC 1965.7.29.165), Sedili River, Johor, Malaysia. A, male pleon; B, F, left G1 (ventral view, denuded); C, G, J, left G1 (dorsal view, denuded); D, H, left distal part of G1 (ventral view, denuded); E, I, left distal part of G1 (dorsal view, denuded). Scales: A = 5.0 mm; B, C, F, G, J = 1.0 mm; D, E, H, I = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351367/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Fig. 40D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA6BA66FFACFE0EFD7CFDA4" blockId="71.[113,753,445,533]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">
Roux’ (1933) record of the species from Palembang in 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFA6BA66FFAFFE6EFF46FE44" box="[114,203,477,501]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
cannot be confirmed. It is retained as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFA6BA66FFACFE4DFEBBFDA4" baseAuthorityName="Miers" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[113,310,510,533]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Miersarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granosimanum">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA6BA66FFACFE4DFEBBFDA4" box="[113,310,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">M. granosimanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until the specimens can be re-examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFA6BA66FFACFD8EFE62FD47" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA6BA66FFACFD8EFE62FD47" blockId="71.[113,753,573,758]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA6BA66FFACFD8EFF4AFDE4" bold="true" box="[113,199,573,597]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Biology</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFA6BA66FF09FD8EFE29FDE4" author="Tweedie" box="[212,420,573,597]" firstAuthor="Tweedie" page="92" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" pagination="88 - 113" refId="ref78385" refString="Tweedie MWF (1940) New and interesting Malaysian species of Sesarma and Utica (Crustacea, Brachyura). Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 16: 88 - 113, figs. 1 - 12, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Tweedie (1940: 92)</bibRefCitation>
writes that he obtained a “good series from fresh-water swamp-forest near the river Sedili, 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFA6BA66FFACFDCEFF3DFD24" box="[113,176,637,661]" country="Malaysia" name="Johor" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Johor</collectingRegion>
. A single specimen from among nipah palms beside the river Sedili, where the water is slightly saline”. The more recent specimens from Muar (ZRC 2002.0162) were collected from behind a mangrove.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFA6BA66FFACFCAEFD02FCE4" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFA6BA66FFACFCAEFD02FCE4" blockId="71.[113,752,797,853]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFA6BA66FFACFCAEFF73FC84" bold="true" box="[113,254,797,821]" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Distribution</emphasis>
. Known from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFA6BA66FDF8FCAEFD06FC84" box="[549,651,797,821]" name="Malaysia" pageId="71" pageNumber="962">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, Borneo, and Sumatra (
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFA6BA66FED7FC8EFE01FCE4" author="Roux" box="[266,396,829,853]" firstAuthor="Roux" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" pagination="1" refId="ref75491" refString="Roux J (1933) Crustaces Decapodes d'eau douce. In: Resultats Scientifiques du Voyage aux Indes Orientales Neerlandaises de LL. AA. RR. le Prince et la Princesse Leopold de Belgique. Memoires du Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique, Hors Serie [= Supplement] 3, No. 14 [= 3 (14)]: 1 - 18, figs. 1, 2." type="journal article" year="1933">Roux, 1933</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFA6BA66FE47FC8EFDB0FCE4" author="Tweedie" box="[410,573,829,853]" firstAuthor="Tweedie" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" pagination="88 - 113" refId="ref78385" refString="Tweedie MWF (1940) New and interesting Malaysian species of Sesarma and Utica (Crustacea, Brachyura). Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 16: 88 - 113, figs. 1 - 12, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Tweedie, 1940</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFA6BA66FD94FC8EFD0EFCE4" author="Tweedie" box="[585,643,829,853]" firstAuthor="Tweedie" pageId="71" pageNumber="962" pagination="338 - 369" refId="ref78455" refString="Tweedie MWF (1950) Grapsoid crabs from Labuan and Sarawak. Sarawak Museum Journal, 5 (2): 338 - 369, figs. 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1950">1950</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
